<paragraph blockId="1.[151,535,1127,1154]" box="[151,535,1127,1154]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,535,1127,1154]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,535,1127,1154]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, [1819]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[238,535,1127,1154]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,339,1127,1154]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Euchloe</emphasis>
Hübner, [1819]
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1193,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
Three, basically parapatric, species of ‘dappled whites’ (genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[873,965,1193,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[873,965,1193,1219]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Euchloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are unanimously recognised to occur in Europe, viz. 1) the eastern dappled white, 2) the mountain dappled white, and 3) the western dappled white. By common consensus, the names [
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[524,606,1265,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[524,606,1265,1291]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Papilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hubner, [1804])" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[626,920,1264,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ausonia">
<emphasis box="[626,715,1266,1291]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">ausonia</emphasis>
(Hübner, [1804])
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyer, 1829" authorityName="Freyer" authorityYear="1829" box="[935,1284,1265,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Pontia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplonia">
<emphasis box="[935,1129,1265,1291]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Pontia simplonia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Freyer, C. F." box="[1139,1284,1265,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="49 - 96" refId="ref5833" refString="Freyer, C. F. (1829) Beitrage zur Geschichte der europaischer Schmetterlinge, mit Abbildungen nach der Natur. 2 Ban d. Bei Verfasser Lit H., in Commission bei den I. Wolff'schen Buchhandlung, Augsburg, 166 pp., pls. 49 - 96." type="book chapter" year="1829">Freyer, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1869" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crameri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Euchloe crameri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Butler, A. G." box="[247,389,1301,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="270 - 273" refId="ref5399" refString="Butler, A. G. (1869) Descriptions of species of Lepidoptera, confounded with others described by Linnaeus and Fabricius. The Entomologist's monthly Magazine, 5, 270 - 273." type="journal article" year="1869">Butler, 1869</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, in the same order, have slowly become fixed to identify them (
<bibRefCitation author="Bernardi, G." box="[1104,1270,1300,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="66 - 103" refId="ref5169" refString="Bernardi, G. (1945) Etudes sur le genre Euchloe Hb. (Lep. Pieridae). Miscellanea entomologica; Revue entomologique internationale, 42 (6), 66 - 103, pls. IV-VI." type="journal article" year="1945">Bernardi 1945</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernardi, G." box="[1281,1340,1301,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref5209" refString="Bernardi, G. (1947) La nomenclature de quelques formes europeennes de l' Euchloe ausonia Hb. (= belia Auct.). Miscellanea entomologica; Revue entomologique internationale, 44 (1), 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1947">1947</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tolman, T. &amp; Lewington, R." pageId="1" pageNumber="388" refId="ref7662" refString="Tolman, T. &amp; Lewington, R. (1997) Butterflies of Britain and Europe. Collins, London, 384 pp." type="book" year="1997">Tolman &amp; Lewington 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tshikolovets, V. V." box="[378,585,1337,1363]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" refId="ref7687" refString="Tshikolovets, V. V. (2011) Butterflies of Europe &amp; the Mediterranean area. V. Tshikolovets, Pardubice, 544 pp." type="book" year="2011">Tshikolovets 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiemers, M. &amp; Balletto, E. &amp; Dinca, V. &amp; Fric, Z. F. &amp; Lamas, G. &amp; Lukhtanov, V. &amp; Munguira, M. L. &amp; van Swaay, C. A. M. &amp; Vila, R. &amp; Vliegenthart, A. &amp; Wahlberg, N. &amp; Verovnik, R." box="[596,825,1337,1363]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="9 - 45" refId="ref7893" refString="Wiemers, M., Balletto, E., Dinca, V., Fric, Z. F., Lamas, G., Lukhtanov, V., Munguira, M. L., van Swaay, C. A. M., Vila, R., Vliegenthart, A., Wahlberg, N. &amp; Verovnik, R. (2018) An updated checklist of the European Butterflies (Lepidoptera, Papilionoidea). ZooKeys, 811, 9 - 45." type="journal article" year="2018">
Wiemers 
<emphasis box="[703,759,1337,1363]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, etc.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="388" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1193,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
Each of these names is riddled with interpretational and nomenclatural problems principally deriving from mismatches between characters shown by the illustrated type materials and their stated type localities. As required by Art. 75.3.1 (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[324,456,1445,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" refId="ref6898" refString="ICZN (1999) (and later updates) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Available from: http: // www. nhm. ac. uk / hosted-sites / iczn / code / (accessed 5 March 2020)" type="url" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
and later updates), these problems will be resolved by designating two 
<typeStatus box="[1274,1388,1445,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">lectotypes</typeStatus>
and two 
<typeStatus box="[200,303,1481,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">neotypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
